[2] Thailand (Surin): human, suspected cat-origin
Date: Mon 31 May 2021
Source: Outbreak News Today [edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/thailand-reports-human-rabies-death-in-surin-67994/


Authorities in Thailand have reported a human rabies death in Surin province in lower northeastern Thailand, according to the Thai news source, Sanook.

The 39-year-old woman looked after 12 cats and 2 dogs. She took in a stray cat that subsequently died. The report doesn't note whether the patient ever received rabies post-exposure prophylaxis.

She started demonstrating symptoms of rabies on 7 May [2021] and died on 15 May [2021] soon after she was laboratory diagnosed.

This is the 1st rabies death reported in Thailand [in 2021], according to the Thailand Bureau of Epidemiology.

In 2020, 3 cases and deaths were reported.

