[On 25-26 Sep 2019, researchers, government officials, and related stakeholders met at an IABS (International Alliance for Biological Standardization) conference in Bangkok, Thailand, to engage on the topic of human rabies mediated by dogs. The objective of the meeting was focused upon snowballing efforts towards achieving substantial progress in rabies prevention, control, and elimination within Asia by 2030, and thereby safeguarding the Pacific region. For the meeting report, go to https://doi.org/10.1016/j.biologicals.2020.01.008. - Mod.AS

