******
[3] Tunisia (Zaghouan): dog, sheep exposed
Date: Tue 1 Jun 2021
Source: Nessma TV [in Arabic, trans. Mod.SF, edited]
https://cutt.ly/unk49bI


The head of the Department of the regional veterinary services of Zaghouan, Areej Jamal, announced today, Tue 1 Jun 2021, the registration of a new animal rabies outbreak in Bir Halima in the governorate of Zaghouan, which is the 3rd outbreak that has been registered since the beginning of this year [2021].

Doctor Jamal said in a statement to the Tunisia African Press Agency that this outbreak was discovered after a dog owned by a sheep breeder was contaminated with this disease from stray dogs, which in turn transmitted it by biting a sheep owned by the same breeder.

She added that the veterinary services, in coordination with the security services, killed all the dogs that had been in contact with the infected dog.

The same interests took the same procedure with regard to the suspected sheep, placing the rest of the herd under quarantine and veterinary monitoring, as well as subjecting a number of citizens of the region to post-exposure prophylaxis.

The head of the department indicated that during the past months of 2021, 2 outbreaks of rabies were discovered in the areas of Muqrin and Bir Halima.

