[Although there are specific regulations for rabies control and a national rabies control program, launched in 1982, the disease remains enzootic in Tunisia. This program calls for collaboration between 3 ministries: the Ministry of Public Health (population awareness/education and post-exposure prophylaxis in humans); the Ministry of Agriculture (veterinary services for free, mass vaccination of carnivores, and surveillance/monitoring programs in animals); and the Ministry of the Interior (dog population management and landfills management).

For animals and humans, the main reservoir and vector of the virus is the dog. Mass vaccination of dogs is the most effective strategy for preventing rabies in humans.

In 2021, 4 human cases of rabies have been registered in Tunisia. - Mod.SF

HealthMap/ProMED map of Tunisia: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=8438528,33382]
